y, systems with compressive stress have an increased hopping ratio and\nconsequently show a preference for ferromagnetic (FM) phases, including,\nunexpectedly, the out-of-plane $d_{3z^2-r^2}$ FM phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Jun 2021 20:01:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Oct 2021 20:44:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-12"}
